<span id="freeTextContainer13481190501160127054">A definite return to form for Bryson after the disappointing &apos;At Home - A Short History of Private Life&apos;.<br/><br/>Who would have thought that there was so much happening in one country in one year? Written with Bryson&apos;s more than usual trademark wit and with his skill of telling otherwise forgotten, obscure or neglected stories in an entertaining, informative and engaging way.<br/><br/>As usual he conveys these stories (connected more of less by the year 1927) with his usual his wide-eyed delivery - sharing his fa</span>
  <span id="freeText13481190501160127054" style="display:none">A definite return to form for Bryson after the disappointing 'At Home - A Short History of Private Life'.<br /><br />Who would have thought that there was so much happening in one country in one year? Written with Bryson's more than usual trademark wit and with his skill of telling otherwise forgotten, obscure or neglected stories in an entertaining, informative and engaging way.<br /><br />As usual he conveys these stories (connected more of less by the year 1927) with his usual his wide-eyed delivery - sharing his fascination with the facts and stories he has unearthed along with the reader.</span>
